%e A363346 In the following diagram, the transient cells on every diagonal are represented by asterisks. This results in the CA to be divided into two regions: ordered behavior on the left, and apparently chaotic behavior on the right. The boundary between the two regions moves to the left, on average, by about 0.252 cells every evolution step (see Wolfram, 2002 and 2019).
